The Washington track and field team headed home from the Oregon Invitational  its second trip to Eugene Ore PERIOD in the past three weeks  with two individual wins and four new NCAA qualifying marks PERIOD As opposed to last time  when the Huskies fell behind the Ducks  several UW athletes shone the brightest PERIOD

The meet was an invitational meaning team scores were not calculated PERIOD Senior Ryan Brown and junior Norris Frederick were the highlights of the weekend as both won their events for the Huskies PERIOD The meet hosted by Oregon featured more than  athletes from  different collegiate teams PERIOD

No stranger to the elite track scene Brown ran to victory in the 800meter dash PERIOD The reigning backtoback indoor and outdoor NCAA champion in the event Browns time of . placed him fifth among college men this year PERIOD

 Brown said PERIOD 

It was Browns sixth straight win in the 800meter final proving he will be one to watch out for at the upcoming Pac10 and NCAA Regional Championships PERIOD However Brown still denies being seen as one of the elites in his event PERIOD

 Brown said PERIOD 

Brown will use that hunger to propel him to his goals at Pac10 and regional championships PERIOD He wants to win Pac10s in the  and score in the top five at regionals he said PERIOD

Also on the mens side Frederick earned titles in the long jump and the high jump PERIOD Frederick started the meet off Friday with a bang by matching his lifetime best in the high jump with a clearance of  inch PERIOD Fredericks momentum carried on to Saturday when he jumped  inches in the long jump PERIOD That distance was a lifetime best for the Seattle native and put him in strong contention for a fifth AllAmerica honor in both events PERIOD

Rounding out competition on the mens side senior Mike Sayenko earned a regional qualifying mark in the  meters while junior Brad Liber earned an NCAA Regional qualifying mark in the  meter steeplechase PERIOD

On the womens side junior Amanda Miller was the highlight of the weekend as she ran an outdoor personal best in the  meters PERIOD Her time of . is the eighthfastest in UW history and earned her a bid to the NCAA regional meet PERIOD

The Huskies returned from Oregon with four new NCAA regional qualifying marks and two athletes who improved their already established regional marks bringing the total number of Huskies with NCAA Regional qualifying marks to  PERIOD
